<subSubSection id="D7D4F44EF0077DDD6738883E877C1372" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="type">
<paragraph id="F2DE2A7E36C37B833821042719C5AA01" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Type:</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4AF76739604B087591F4BDBB896465A" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">India. Mishmi Hills, Griffith s.n. (holotype: K!, K000396854).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="069850D7B37F4A787707AB6597D31239" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="note">
<paragraph id="CBE17D1DE65DC5295D26CDAAD3FD975C" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Note:</paragraph>
<paragraph id="562789ECF7E0B7A44F1F6229FA1F63F4" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
As noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="1E9A46BB17CB055EB42F2A1567E80354" author="Hooker, JD" editor="Hooker, JD" journalOrPublisher="2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 388" refId="B6" refString="Hooker, JD, 1878. Rosaceae. In: Hooker, JD, Ed., Flora of British India, vol. 2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London: 307 - 388" title="Rosaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of British India, vol." year="1878">Hooker (1878)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="727E67A4B7E9B66C743CDB6BD3551E0A" class="Mammalia" family="Astrapotheriidae" genus="Maddenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Astrapotheria" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pedicellata">
<emphasis id="7320F79E99DE4CEBDFD67C54EB4D5B90" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Maddenia pedicellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a fragmentary specimen collected by Griffith from the Mishmi Hills. It was stated to be characterized by subcorymbose flowers on long slender pedicels on a short peduncle in unripe fruits (
<bibRefCitation id="26FEF932C22E756152EAEB6C75F6FE23" author="Hooker, JD" editor="Hooker, JD" journalOrPublisher="2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 388" refId="B6" refString="Hooker, JD, 1878. Rosaceae. In: Hooker, JD, Ed., Flora of British India, vol. 2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London: 307 - 388" title="Rosaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of British India, vol." year="1878">Hooker 1878</bibRefCitation>
, p. 318). The type was mounted on a sheet with 
<taxonomicName id="4968D978B19F5549E95208B38F4C7AFF" authorityName="J. Wen" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gongshanensis">
<emphasis id="2B4B7B41DE1C6ABE509CF15B091CCE8E" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Prunus gongshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Bhutan (Griffith 2057, K) in flower condition, although 
<bibRefCitation id="CFFFB46C1F94E7B301D966EB826B1126" author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Japanese Botany" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="7 - 11" refId="B4" refString="Hara, H, 1976. New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17). Journal of Japanese Botany 51 (1): 7 - 11" title="New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17)." volume="51" year="1976">Hara (1976)</bibRefCitation>
said it was a collection of 
<taxonomicName id="447E81FED57E5CC5C6671BDD01A04BC9" authorityName="Hook fil &amp; Thomson" authorityYear="1854" class="Mammalia" family="Astrapotheriidae" genus="Maddenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Astrapotheria" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="himalaica">
<emphasis id="EE778EA1880DECF35C725837D9AAB147" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Maddenia himalaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which should bear highly pubescent leaves. This specimen has glabrous lower leaf surfaces with only traces of hairs at the axils of veins on the lower leaves. Our examination of the type material confirms 
<normalizedToken id="B7490F49BF5B6A2AA819096F869EFAAB" originalValue="Haraâ€™s">Hara's</normalizedToken>
treatment of 
<taxonomicName id="00C3BC9B8651E8F7B522368A068C0234" class="Mammalia" family="Astrapotheriidae" genus="Maddenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Astrapotheria" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pedicellata">
<emphasis id="F60360D0FE04E3682C8E69D25FFF8697" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Maddenia pedicellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="AE9012AA8345ABA8DA82F3351518F695" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cerasoides">
<emphasis id="44F18C53020095E9B57F3D1E4B257BC6" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Prunus cerasoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Buchanan-Hamilton ex D. Don (
<bibRefCitation id="3189349F6A53494522B7CD61D2112CB2" author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Japanese Botany" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="7 - 11" refId="B4" refString="Hara, H, 1976. New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17). Journal of Japanese Botany 51 (1): 7 - 11" title="New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17)." volume="51" year="1976">Hara 1976</bibRefCitation>
; also see 
<bibRefCitation id="D6A2A7800AE5DDAF599B25CB2F4E03C3" author="Lu, L" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="9. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="46 - 434" refId="B10" refString="Lu, L, Gu, C, Li, C, Alexander, C, Bartholomew, B, Brach, A, Boufford, DE, Ikeda, H, Ohba, H, Robertson, KR, Spongberg, SA, 2003. Rosaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., , Flora of China, vol. 9. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 46 - 434" title="Rosaceae." volumeTitle=", Flora of China, vol." year="2003">Lu et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
